ded through international agreements to return Armenian properties, it continues to refuse to do so. The book demonstrates that genocides do not depend on the abolition of the legal system and elimination of rights, but that, on the contrary, the perpetrators of genocide manipulate the legal system to facilitate their plans.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aArmenian question. 0aArmeniansxLegal status, laws, etc.zTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 0aArmeniansxRelocationzTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 0aArmenianszTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 0aForced migrationzTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 0aPillagezTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Genocide & War Crimes.2bisacsh1 aKurt, Umit, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311099823840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782386247?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782386247423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782386247/original  a978-3-11-099823-8  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK